● Here's the full picture. Your project is Makefile-based (no CMakeLists.txt), and composing builds to bin/composing from MyHatTileStuff/composing.o + the core objects. Two things will bite you if you don't address them:

  1. No debug symbols. CFLAGS = -O3 -Wall -Wextra -std=c11 — there's no -g, and -O3 makes stepping/variable inspection nearly useless. You must rebuild with -g -O0.
  2. Relative paths. main() takes no args, but it reads a tile file and writes img/composing.svg using relative paths, so the working directory must be the project root (/home/jmartin/CLionProjects/PolyformTown/PolyformTown), not bin/ or a cmake-build-* dir.

  CLion configuration

  1. Tell CLion this is a Makefile project

  If it currently opened as something else, do File → Close Project, then Open the project root — CLion auto-detects the Makefile. (You already have compile_commands.json too, but it only covers centers.c, so rely on the Makefile here.)

  2. Create a Custom Build Target

  Settings → Build, Execution, Deployment → Custom Build Targets → +
  - Name: composing
  - Toolchain: your default (System GCC/GDB)
  - Build → click ... → + to add an external tool:
    - Program: make
    - Arguments: composing CFLAGS="-g -O0 -Wall -Wextra -std=c11"
    - Working directory: $ProjectFileDir$
  - Clean (optional) → another tool: make with args clean (or just rebuild manually).

  The CFLAGS="..." override is what injects debug symbols. Note: this overrides the Makefile's CFLAGS, so I dropped -O3 and added -g -O0. The -I$(SRC) is added separately by the pattern rule, so you don't need it here.

  ▎ If you'd rather not pass CFLAGS each time, edit line 3 of the Makefile to CFLAGS = -g -O0 -Wall -Wextra -std=c11 and just use make composing as the build command. Then make clean composing once to force a rebuild of the .o files (otherwise the stale -O3 objects get reused).

  3. Create a Run/Debug configuration

  Run → Edit Configurations → + → Custom Build Application
  - Target: composing (the custom build target above)
  - Executable: bin/composing
  - Program arguments: (none)
  - Working directory: /home/jmartin/CLionProjects/PolyformTown/PolyformTown (project root — critical for the relative img/... and tile paths)

  4. Debug

  Set a breakpoint in composing.c, click the bug icon. GDB will stop and let you inspect since the objects now carry -g -O0.

